---
import { pagePath } from "../data/site";
---

<section class="what-is">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <h2>What is Breachwalker?</h2>
    <p>
      Breachwalker is a web-first expedition survival game from Benum Labs. The
      Hold — a marginal institution born from a Walker's discovery — recruits
      breachers to enter rifts where corrupted ledger entries have cracked open.
      You stand on the surface hold, select a rift from the ledger, and breach
      inward — managing stamina, fighting through procedurally derived space,
      and deciding when to extract loot to your vault.
    </p>
    <p>
      Each catalog entry is a different wound in the Record, so danger, scale,
      and density vary rift by rift. The closed alpha tests whether that loop is
      worth returning to before marketplace trade and item NFTs on Base join the
      picture.
    </p>
    <p class="what-is__links muted">
      <a href={pagePath("/how-it-works")}>How the breach loop works</a>
      ·
      <a href={pagePath("/bitcoin-rifts")}>Why the ledger becomes rifts</a>
      ·
      <a href={pagePath("/extraction-survival-game")}>Extraction survival</a>
      ·
      <a href={pagePath("/item-economy")}>Item economy</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .what-is {
    padding: var(--space-2xl) 0;
  }

  .what-is h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .what-is p {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .what-is__links {
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
  }

  .what-is__links a {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .what-is__links a:hover {
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }
</style>
